      "writtenOn": "2017-11-19T21:45:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "here we assume that getDatacenter logs errors (otherwise we just loose err). Better not to assume that. If you move logging from getDatacenters here, then the overall number of lines will actually decrease\n\nstepping back, it looks we will need to log internal errors not only here, but any RPC method. Consider\n\n  // internalRPCError logs the error and returns an internal GRPC error\n  // with message \"Internal server error\"\n  func internalRPCError(c context.Context, err error) err\n\n(the rationale for `message \"Internal server error\"` is that we might not want to expose the internal details to users)\n\nand use it in all RPC methods like\n\n  return nil, internalRPCError(c, err)",
