    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7652f5ce_a7fa196a",
        "filename": "machine-db/appengine/model/datacenters/datacenters_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 42,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-22T00:06:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done, but the reason it was this way is because I believe that unit tests should be black box tests which call a function with some arguments and assert the output without caring what the function actually did to produce those results. It\u0027s antithetical to that style of testing to assert the specific details of everything the unit under test does.\n\nIdeally for testing I\u0027d be using an in-memory MySQL database which actually executes the statements, then in the Convey I\u0027d just populate the database, provide a config for the EnsureDatacenters call, and assert what\u0027s in the database at the end without caring what SQL statements were executed by EnsureDatacenters to achieve that result.",
      "parentUuid": "20490155_ac2554a3",
